                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
$BR
(b) If \( t=-\frac{\pi}{2} \), then \(x=\) \{ans_rule(15) \} 
                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
$BR
(c) If \( t=\frac{\pi}{3} \), then \(x=\) \{ans_rule(15) \} 
                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
$BR
(d) If \( t=-\frac{\pi}{3} \), then \(x=\) \{ans_rule(15) \} 
                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
$BR
(e) If \( t=\frac{3\pi}{4} \), then \(x=\) \{ans_rule(15) \} 
                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
$BR
(f) If \( t=-\frac{3\pi}{4} \), then \(x=\) \{ans_rule(15) \} 
                               and \(y=\) \{ans_rule(15) \}; 
END_TEXT

